      "id": "PopularPost314988",
      "post_content": "I've been running a black/red bloodhound deck. The key is to use [treacherous link](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=treacherous link) with [crypt rats](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=crypt rats) or [thrashing wumpus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=thrashing wumpus). Put a [vampiric link](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= vampiric link) on crypt rats and boom. If you have a treacherous link on the rats and a bloodhound you can clear the board most likely and super pump your blood hound . Double life link rats and they have no chance and your wolves are huge lol. Does depend on black alot but, you can use a fling or something similar for a quick strike. For a creature removal spell i sugeest [ashes to ashes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=ashes to ashes). Maybe use [simulacrum](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=simulacrum)? Demons with their strong abilities and their painful (downsides) are something i was thinking about. What do you guys think? ",
      "posted_by": "gremloc",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost314988\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">I've been running a black/red bloodhound deck. The key is to use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"treacherous link\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=treacherous link\">treacherous link</a> with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"crypt rats\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=crypt rats\">crypt rats</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"thrashing wumpus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=thrashing wumpus\">thrashing wumpus</a>. Put a<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\" vampiric link\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= vampiric link\"> vampiric link</a> on crypt rats and boom. If you have a treacherous link on the rats and a bloodhound you can clear the board most likely and super pump your blood hound . Double life link rats and they have no chance and your wolves are huge lol. Does depend on black alot but, you can use a fling or something similar for a quick strike.  For a creature removal spell i sugeest <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"ashes to ashes\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=ashes to ashes\">ashes to ashes</a>. Maybe use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"simulacrum\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=simulacrum\">simulacrum</a>? Demons with their strong abilities and their painful (downsides) are something i was thinking about. What do you guys think? </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '314988'); return false;\">\r\n          