    {
      "id": "PopularPost328690",
      "post_content": "IT SPECIFIES AT THE BEGINNING OF YOUR END STEP!  \n  \nYou know what that means?  \n  \n[Sundial of the Infinite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sundial of the Infinite) stops it from losing counters, since you skip your end step and it's not an end of turn thing. So hey, very angry hound. If you're having trouble from lack of evasion, you can activate Sundial and play [Madcap Skills](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Madcap Skills) in the space of the same amount of mana it costs to play Blood Hound. So hey, up to you.  \n  \nLittle weird that it says end of turn on the card though. Must be because of the whole \"gets counters on anyone's turn but only loses them on yours\" thing.",
      "posted_by": "NARFNra",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost328690\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">IT SPECIFIES AT THE BEGINNING OF YOUR END STEP!<br/><br/>You know what that means?<br/><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sundial of the Infinite\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sundial of the Infinite\">Sundial of the Infinite</a> stops it from losing counters, since you skip your end step and it's not an end of turn thing. So hey, very angry hound. If you're having trouble from lack of evasion, you can activate Sundial and play <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Madcap Skills\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Madcap Skills\">Madcap Skills</a> in the space of the same amount of mana it costs to play Blood Hound. So hey, up to you.<br/><br/>Little weird that it says end of turn on the card though. Must be because of the whole \"gets counters on anyone's turn but only loses them on yours\" thing.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '328690'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy48472\">NARFNra</span>\r\n                                (7/12/2013 7:48:27 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n         