    {
      "id": "PopularPost377061",
      "post_content": "I've played variations on a casual deck with this guy for years. [Flame Rift](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flame Rift), [Ancient Tomb](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancient Tomb) and [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling) were the obvious ones around the time when he came out, but when [Tarnished Citadel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tarnished Citadel) came out during Odyssey that was the final piece. I'd play a deck that only needed to successfully attack with him once, and it was pretty easy to keep the board clear in red, and then I'd play [Final Fortune](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Final Fortune) to repeat. The counters build up fast when you're killing yourself with the tombs and the citadels. [Lava Hounds](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lava Hounds) is another obvious buddy. The deck I run them in is red and white, you can play life gain cards like [Life Burst](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Life Burst) in case you're getting a bit too close when getting the combo ready, but in general, you only need to get the Hound to attack once to get some necessary cards in motion. One of my favorite Johnny cards. ",
      "posted_by": "HawkeaterMoth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost377061\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">I've played variations on a casual deck with this guy for years. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flame Rift\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flame Rift\">Flame Rift</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ancient Tomb\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancient Tomb\">Ancient Tomb</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fling\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling\">Fling</a> were the obvious ones around the time when he came out, but when <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tarnished Citadel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tarnished Citadel\">Tarnished Citadel</a> came out during Odyssey that was the final piece. I'd play a deck that only needed to successfully attack with him once, and it was pretty easy to keep the board clear in red, and then I'd play <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Final Fortune\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Final Fortune\">Final Fortune</a> to repeat. The counters build up fast when you're killing yourself with the tombs and the citadels. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lava Hounds\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lava Hounds\">Lava Hounds</a> is another obvious buddy. The deck I run them in is red and white, you can play life gain cards like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Life Burst\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Life Burst\">Life Burst</a> in case you're getting a bit too close when getting the combo ready, but in general, you only need to get the Hound to attack once to get some necessary cards in motion. One of my favorite Johnny cards. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '377061'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy108349\">HawkeaterMoth</span>\r\n                                (5/24/2014 10:43:27 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
